metadata.name: Rukobia 600 mg 1 Tablet film coated extended release

clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Fostemsavir is indicated in combination with other antiretrovirals for the treatment of multidrug resistant HIV 1 infection in heavily treatment experienced adults failing their current antiretroviral therapy due to resistance intolerance or safety concerns L14867

contraindications.disease: Data regarding fostemsavir overdose are unavailable L14867 Symptoms of overdose are likely to be consistent with fostemsavir s adverse effect profile and may therefore involve significant GI disturbance and prolongation of the QT interval L14867 In the event of overdose patients should be monitored closely including the use of ECG and treated symptomatically as clinically indicated As fostemsavir is highly protein bound dialysis is unlikely to be of benefit in the event of an overdose L14867
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Temsavir inhibits the first stage in the HIV 1 viral lifecycle attachment L14867 It has a moderate duration of action necessitating twice daily dosing L14867 Fostemsavir administered at roughly 4x the recommended human dose has been observed to significantly prolong the QTc interval Patients with a history of QTc prolongation those receiving other QTc prolonging medications and or those with pre existing cardiac disease should use fostemsavir with caution and should be monitored at baseline and throughout therapy for signs or symptoms suggestive of QTc prolongation L14867 Fostemsavir should also be used with caution in patients with hepatitis B or C co infection as elevations in hepatic transaminases were observed in greater proportions in these populations in clinical trials L14867
